<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-473-107  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 473 107.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Journal of Systems Management  Sept 1990 v41 n9 p23(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Is IS ripe for malpractice suits? (information systems)(Lookinginto the Future) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Aeh, Richard K.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The law may force information systems (IS) professionals toconduct themselves more professionally, rather than allowing theprofessionals themselves to raise their own standards voluntarily.andO;Certain professionals, such as doctors or lawyers, can be sued formalpractice, according to the law, for not acting as aprofessional should; IS professionals may be added to the list dueto a ruling made by a US court in Missouri.andP;  In DiversifiedGraphics v. Groves, an appellate court upheld a verdict that amanufacturer in St. Louis could sue an accounting firm for faultycomputer services based on the grounds that it had actedunprofessionally.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MISLaw SuitProfessionalismLiabilityLegal IssuesManagement Style.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>